source.name: Campgrounds by County Outside Adirondack & Catskill Forest Preserve Map
source.description: The points map shows the location of state campgrounds outside the Adirondack and Catskill Forest Preserve. Clicking a pin point on the map, will bring up a flyout with information about the campground. The New York State Office of Parks, Recreation and Historic Preservation oversees 179 state parks and 35 historic sites, which are visited by 60 million people annually. The New York State Office of Parks and Recreation operates campgrounds in 65 state parks across New York (outside the Adirondack and Catskill Forest Preserves) offering more than 9,000 campsites, cabins and cottages.
